04096nam a22005535i 9780889208582DE-B159720240306125748.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20061984xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97808892085827 a10.51644/97808892085822doi  a(DE-B1597)667203  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 4aPR3458P6 7aBIO0070002bisacsh04a016.823qOCoLC1 aCleary, Thomas R., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aHenry Fielding :bA Political Writer /cThomas R. Cleary. 1aWaterloo, Ontario : bWilfrid Laurier University Press, c[2006] 4c©1984  a1 online resource (366 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFront Matter -- tContents -- tList of Abbreviations -- tAcknowledgements -- tIntroduction -- tProlegomena: George Lyttelton, the Broad-Bottoms, and the Pattern of Fielding's Political Career -- tFielding's Early Career: 1728-35 -- tPasquin and the Haymarket: 1736-37 -- tThe Final Assault on Walpole: 1739-42 -- tFielding and the "New" Opposition: 1742-44 -- tFielding and the Jacobites, 1745-49: The True Patriot to Tom Jones -- tThe Final Phase: 1749-54 -- tNotes -- tSelective Bibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAn accurate and comprehensive study of the political aspects of Fielding's art has been sorely needed. As a result of decades of work by literary scholars and a series of great historians, such a study is finally possible. This volume addresses that need, and, in the light of a recent revival of interest in Fielding's work, it arrives most opportunely. The author offers here a wide-ranging focus and a firm grip on the shifting complexities of Fielding's political situations—the loyalties and enmities, factional alignments and fractious rhetoric—that allow the satisfactory understanding of Fielding's political writing. Political writing in Fielding's day, as in ours, was topical, concerned with evanescent problems and day-to-day needs that were familiar to contemporaries, but that are now recaptured only with greatest difficulty. This study constitutes a thorough reconstruction of Fielding's political context and extricates from the context Fielding's own political endeavours. Cleary's work will make many of Fielding's previously unstudied works accessible to students and scholars of eighteenth-century English literature. A necessary point of reference to both literary specialists and historians concerned with eighteenth-century England.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical fiction, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitics and literaturexHistoryx18th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aPolitics and literaturezGreat BritainxHistoryy18th century. 4aLiterary Criticism. 4aPolitical Science. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920858240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889208582423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889208582/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles